reviews.review_text: Food: Overall, it was delicious Japanese burgers. They are smaller than the average Western burger. Really delicious, unique, and fresh burgers. Juicy patties with lots of filling, between two soft buns. The corn dog, on the other hand, is a bit disappointing. Its not as tasty as the burgers. Favourite dish(es): Chicken Cutlet, Teriyaki Burger Service: Usually, one person is behind the counter. Great customer service. Other Comments: Check out the Street Food Vancouver app for their locations and hours. Recommend: Definitely a yes!

My favorite burger in Vancouver. If you re looking for amazing food, amazing service, and great experience then Wakwak is for you. They treat you like royalty, with an amazing smile. My favorite burger is the deluxe Teryaki cheese   heavenly !!
The regular burger is great value since it is freshly made and especially appreciated the caramelized onions in it, which help amplify the flavour.

First time trying Wak Wak Burger after seeing it parked in my neighbourhood for many months. It was delicious! We had the Pork Tonkatsu burger and the Japanese Chicken Cutlet burger. Both were very good and enormous! The pork was bigger than the bun and the sauces were a perfect balance. Generous portion of cabbage made it feel like I got my daily requirement of veggies. Cant wait to try other menu items!
Good burger with Starbucks drink I met them in kitsilano food market last summer. Still taste good as usual Recommended dishes
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much.  We will be open Kitsilano beach   Summer. Thank you.

reviews.review_text: I came across this burger truck while walking down Granville Street. The price got me to stop and look and the interesting Japanese style burgers got me to try and buy. I ordered the okonomi burger just because Ive never tried one. It was great and hit the spot. The only negative was the wait to order the food and the wait to get the food. Understanding it was lunch time it didnt take more than 6 min for both. If you need a quick bite, I can recommend this place.

One of the cheapest and best burger places in downtown Vancouver! This place is renowned for their famous $2.85 burger. I highly recommend you try one of these. I love these so much that I unintentionally took a bite out of mine before I took a picture of it. Also, quick tip: if the patty seems too thin, then get a double burger for only a dollar extra. Give it a try!

I didnt think Vancouver would have its own cheap burger stop that could stack up to other regional chains like In-N-Out or Shakeshack. Theyve got Bin 4, which is phenomenal-- but theyre definitely in the premium range of burger restaurants, which you cant really compare with street food or fast food, especially considering the hefty price. Wakwak, despite not being a chain, hits that cheap, quality burger craving perfectly. For me, its a bit of a trip, but always worth stopping by whenever Im downtown. Tried 4 items on their menu and all of them were fantastic. And with burgers these good starting at 2.85, you really cant complain.

Come on, folks. You cant complain about the value of this burger unless youre trying to run this wholesome place out of business. You get a fresh-tasting burger, with the option of making it messy but even tastier with their sauce (and topping) options. With fries and a drink, it makes for a decent meal thats around $10. Their sweet mozzarella corn dog is an absolute treat that belongs at all fairs - a crunchy, sugary, donut-like exterior with a gooey cheesy centre (more cheese to dog ratio). Plus, the staff is so energetic and all smiles. I only wish they would sell weekly in front of my workplace..
We ve order cheese burger and Chicken Namban. I missed chicken namban so tried it:) it was very tasty and saucey, so eat it at home haha. Will try them next time they comes to River District!
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you so much.See you soon.

reviews.review_text: The omotenashi of the Japanese is always top notch, even when they are crammed in a small burger trailer on the sidewalk on Granville street! The burgers are very good with a sweet tang to them, the fries are crispy and not oily, and the place is cheap! Its a great stop for a quick, satisfying lunch or snack.
Home of the Japanese style wakwak burger.   Scrumptious, budget friendly street burgers, that you need to consume fast.... For three dollars you really can not go wrong.

This food cart reminds me of Japadog with their hot dogs.  Here they start with a great burger and explore it s possibilities.  I like how they infuse Japanese flavour and creativity to each item.  Cheaper and tastes way better than McD.
This is an absolute must if you are in town. Delicious, cheap and all around awesome! We need more places like this in Vancouver. Keep it up guys

Great burgers! . I wish they understood social media and made use of it. No postings about future locations, only post location on the day of. So basically impossible to plan to go there. Website is in Korean with no English translation. You will find great success with active promotion!
Amazing burgers. Love the Deluxe and Okonomi. Yum!  Japanese Style delicious burgers
I got a Teriyaki Burger. The ingredients are of great quality and. The taste is really good and very truthful. The service is excellent, very quick!
Very good and cheap burgers. They also had a veggie burger option for an extra $0.25. Quick and friendly service.
Pretty good teriyaki burger the only problem most of the time you don t find them In one place
What a nice smile to welcome you ! The food is great with a really fair price ! The large portion of fries is enormous ! And I LOVE that he is including the taxes on his price !!
Fantastic cheap eats. Genuine workers who always seem happy to have you there. One of the few truly hospitable street joints in Metro Van.
Oh my, their burger and fries toppings are delicious. I miss studying near Granville just to wait for the bus while eating their fresh fries
reviews.response_from_owner_text: Thank you  Please come back when you have time. We look forward to seeing you soon. Sincerely

reviews.review_text: Loved the price and the burgers were really good. They also toasted the bun a bit so they were a bit crispy. The line was a bit long but it was Friday afternoon when I had dropped by but the service was very friendly. The staff kept apologizing for the wait! Will definitely return again!

So these are cheap burgers. Not just inexpensive, but cheap, maybe Costco burgers. Thats not a complaint: theyre around 3 bucks even if you get a fancy sauce one, they taste good, theyre piping hot, and the location is convenient. Better option than any of the fast food burgers around here (ok, Fatburger is better, but costs more than twice as much).

Cheap for sure. Tastes good - like any decent burger. Size portion a bit small - like maybe 10 to 20 percent smaller than a McChicken. But for 3 dollars, a burger and that too in downtown vancouver - wins everyday!
Delicious and cheap food truck! The tori ten burger was especially good and we also enjoyed the okonomi burger and fries with all the toppings.

Wow, surpisingly good. Was going to get some food from Fatburger, but they are not open today. Spotted this place on my walk back to my car and decided to give it a try. Got a teriyaki burger and fries and a can of coke for under $9 and all were very good. The patty is thin and portion was a little on the small side for me, but for $9, it was great.

We visited their food truck location on Cambie (across whole foods) for lunch. The double burger and teriyaki burger were both delicious and freshly made. They were extremely kind and friendly and we will definitely be going back. :)

Most delicious affordable burger I have ever eaten. The people are super nice who serve there and it is totally worth the wait for one of their burgers. Their fries are also really good. But their burgers are a dream.

You want a burger? These are the burgers you want. They come out so hot that I burn my mouth almost every time. I could just let them cool down if I had any self control, but here we are, covered in cheese and teriyaki. My beard and hands are sticky, and I want another burger now.
Contender of the best burger in Vancouver, for 2/3 of the price of a burger from a traditional fast food joint. Very highly recommended!
Cant beat the prices and burgers are amazing
Good value for a 3 dollar burger!  The patty is quite thin but very wide.  Bun is nicely toasted.
Super yummy!! Nice and friendly staff make us Japanese style burger, and very reasonable!
A great burger and genuinely some of the nicest people operating the Food Truck. Okonomi burger was great!
Probably the best 2.99 burger you ll find. Fresh ingredients and nicely cooked patty, you can t go wrong.
Delicious delicious burgers and their veggie patties are great too!! Would heavily recommend thrit okonomi burger!!!
Delicious, affordable, and handy. Today, I found them at the side of Hinge park(Tuesday). I hope theyll come here regularly. No cooking on Tuesdays
Real good place to grab a small bite. Amazing cook who has really good energy. Love the burgers.

First day in vancouver and we stopped by wakwak to have 2 great burgers. Sometimes the simplest things are the best, and this was the case!
Very good burger especially accounting for its price. The food is not healthy. Shocker.
Perfect size great prices delicious burgers and omg the fries crunch with the fluffy inside yuummy
Loved the teriyaki cheeseburger! Impossible to get a better burger for the same price.
The food truck was parked at Main & 14th today. Ordered the cheeseburger and fries - oh yum! Didn t wait long at all - highly recommend!
Delicious food at reasonable prices. Vancouvers best value burger.
Awesome burger from a food truck. So simple, so cheap,  so delicious.  The teriyaki sauce seals the deal.

I was walking by and decided to try a burger. I wish I had a second one. Delicious burger will definitely go back.
